main event: A white object the size of a first magnitude star was observed passing across the sky in the Pacific Ocean on May 6, 1964.
interesting points: The object was observed at very high altitude, along a course connecting the stars Dubhe and Polaris, passing through the Big Dipper and Polaris.
The object was observed for a duration of 5 minutes, or 105 seconds.
The observer was unable to evaluate the object further.
The sighting was reported through a CIRVIS (Communication Instructions for Reporting Vital Intelligence Sightings) report.
The sighting was located at coordinates 30-20N 176-00W in the Pacific Ocean.
sighted object: a white object the size of a first magnitude star
